paap ( english : sin ) is a 2003 indian hindi film , directed by pooja bhatt in her directorial debut , and features john abraham , udita goswami , gulshan grover and mohan agashe . though the film did not fare well at the box office , it received considerable critical acclaim , especially for its cinematography , direction and mahesh bhatt 's indianised adaptation of peter weir 's 1985 english film witness . the film is also remembered for its soundtrack , which featured numerous pakistani artists , and also marked the bollywood debut of singer rahat fateh ali khan with mann ki lagan , thus setting a trend of pakistani singers in bollywood .